config AKIRA_BT_HID
    bool "Enable Bluetooth HID"
    default n
    depends on AKIRA_HID && BT
    help
      Enable HID over Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE).
      Requires Bluetooth stack to be enabled.

config AKIRA_BT_ECHO
    bool "Enable Bluetooth Echo service"
    default n
    depends on BT
    help
      Enable a small developer GATT Echo service. The service receives writes
      and echoes the payload back via notifications. Useful for testing and
      debugging BT connectivity. Can also be toggled at runtime via shell.

config AKIRA_BT_COMPANION
    bool "Enable Bluetooth Companion Service"
    default n
    depends on BT && BT_PERIPHERAL && BT_GATT_DYNAMIC_DB
    help
      Enable the AkiraOS Companion GATT service used by the AkiraApp mobile
      application (Android / iOS).  Provides BLE-based remote management:
      app install/uninstall, OTA firmware update, settings read/write, device
      status notifications, shell command passthrough, and LittleFS file
      browser.

      Mutually exclusive with BT_MODE_HID — only one BLE mode may be active
      at a time.  The active mode is selected from the Settings menu or via
      the shell command 'bt mode companion'.

      Requires BT_MAX_CONN >= 1 and BT_GATT_DYNAMIC_DB=y.

config AKIRA_BT_COMPANION_STATUS_INTERVAL_MS
    int "Companion status notification interval (ms)"
    default 60000
    range 5000 300000
    depends on AKIRA_BT_COMPANION
    help
      How often the device pushes an unsolicited device.status notification
      to a connected companion app.  Default 60 seconds matches the cloud
      heartbeat interval.

config AKIRA_BT_COMPANION_MAX_TRANSFER_KB
    int "Maximum BLE file/app transfer size (kB)"
    default 512
    range 16 2048
    depends on AKIRA_BT_COMPANION
    help
      Maximum size of a single file or app binary transferred over BLE.
      Affects the size of the staging buffer allocated at transfer start.
      Ensure adequate heap is available (PSRAM recommended).

