config AKIRA_WASM_NET
    bool "Export Network API to WASM (TCP/UDP sockets)"
    default n
    depends on AKIRA_WASM_API && (NET_TCP || NET_UDP)
    help
      Export a stream-based TCP/UDP socket API to WASM applications.
      Data flows through shared-memory ring buffers in WASM linear memory,
      minimising WASM/host context switches.
      Requires 'network' capability in the app manifest.

config AKIRA_NET_MAX_STREAMS
    int "Maximum concurrent network streams"
    default 4
    range 1 16
    depends on AKIRA_WASM_NET
    help
      Number of simultaneous TCP/UDP socket slots available.
      Each slot uses a small amount of SRAM for metadata.
      Actual data buffers live in WASM linear memory (PSRAM).

config AKIRA_NET_POLL_STACK_SIZE
    int "Network poll thread stack size (bytes)"
    default 2048
    range 1024 8192
    depends on AKIRA_WASM_NET
    help
      Stack size of the internal poll thread that drives all sockets.
      The stack must accommodate a per-call RX buffer of
      CONFIG_AKIRA_NET_MAX_MSG_SIZE bytes.

config AKIRA_NET_EVENT_QUEUE_DEPTH
    int "Network event queue depth (messages)"
    default 8
    range 4 32
    depends on AKIRA_WASM_NET
    help
      Number of network events (CONNECTED, DATA_READY, ACCEPT, etc.)
      that can be buffered before the WASM app drains them with
      net_event_pop().

config AKIRA_NET_MAX_MSG_SIZE
    int "Maximum single network message size (bytes)"
    default 1500
    range 64 4096
    depends on AKIRA_WASM_NET
    help
      Maximum payload size for a single framed message in the TX/RX ring.
      Should match or exceed the network MTU (1500 for Ethernet/WiFi).
      Used to size the temporary receive buffer on the poll thread stack.

